quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  3,130,"O ye who believe! devour not usury, doubling it again and again! But fear God, that ye may prosper"
  3,131,And fear the fire which is prepared for them that believe not
  3,132,"and obey God and the apostle, that ye may find mercy"
  3,133,"And vie in haste for pardon from your Lord, and a Paradise, vast as the Heavens and the Earth, prepared for the God-fearing"
  3,134,"Who give alms, alike in prosperity and in success, and who master their anger, and forgive others! God loveth the doers of good"
  3,135,"They who, after they have done a base deed or committed a wrong against their own selves, remember God and implore forgiveness of their sins - and who will forgive sins but God only? - and persevere not in what they have wittingly done amiss"
  3,136,"As for these! Pardon from their Lord shall be their recompense, and gardens 'neath which the rivers flow; for ever shall they abide therein: And goodly the reward of those who labour"
  3,137,"Already, before your time, have examples been made! Traverse the earth, then, and see what hath been the end of those who treat prophets as liars"
  3,138,"This Koran is a manifest to man, and a guidance, and a warning to the God-fearing"
  3,139,"And be not fainthearted, and be not sorrowful: For ye shall gain the upper hand if ye be believers"
  3,140,"If a wound hath befallen you, a wound like it hath already befallen others: we alternate these days of successes and reverses among men, that God may know those who have believed, and that He may take martyrs from among you, - but God loveth not the wrongful doers"
  3,141,"And that God may test those who believe, and destroy the infidels"
  3,142,"Thought ye that ye should enter Paradise ere God had taken knowledge of those among you who did valiantly, and of those who steadfastly endure"
  3,143,Ye had desired death ere ye met it. But ye have now seen it - and ye have beheld it - and fled from it